1
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:19,812
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

2
00:00:19,854 --> 00:00:21,605
HOSHI: Bridge to Mayweather.

3
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:35,828
TRAVIS: MAYWEATHER.

4
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:37,872
HOSHI: The captain wants you
to report to the bridge.

5
00:00:37,913 --> 00:00:39,832
Admiral Forrest called
a few minutes ago.

6
00:00:39,874 --> 00:00:41,834
We're reversing course.

7
00:00:41,876 --> 00:00:44,043
TRAVIS: I'M ON MY WAY.

8
00:00:47,006 --> 00:00:49,842
SINGER: ♪ IT'S BEEN
A LONG ROAD ♪

9
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:54,805
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

10
00:00:54,847 --> 00:00:58,684
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

11
00:00:58,726 --> 00:01:02,646
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

12
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:06,859
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

13
00:01:06,901 --> 00:01:10,404
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

14
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:14,199
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

15
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:17,327
♪ NO, THEY'RE
NOT GONNA CHANGE MY MIND ♪

16
00:01:17,369 --> 00:01:20,414
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

17
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,207
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

18
00:01:22,249 --> 00:01:25,669
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

19
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:30,507
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

20
00:01:30,549 --> 00:01:33,510
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

21
00:01:33,552 --> 00:01:38,390
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

22
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,976
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA
BEND OR BREAK ME ♪

23
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:46,523
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

24
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:47,858
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

25
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,277
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

26
00:01:50,318 --> 00:01:54,364
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

27
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:58,493
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

28
00:02:10,923 --> 00:02:13,008
T'POL:
THE PLANET'S ORBIT HAS SHIFTED,

29
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:15,052
TAKING IT BETWEEN
TWO GAS GIANTS.

30
00:02:15,094 --> 00:02:17,554
THEIR GRAVITATIONAL PULL IS
CAUSING ITS CORE TO SUPERHEAT.

31
00:02:17,596 --> 00:02:19,222
ARCHER: STARFLEET THINKS
IT'LL BE COVERED

32
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:22,601
WITH ERUPTING VOLCANOES
BY THE END OF THE WEEK.

33
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:25,896
TRAVIS: THIS SYSTEM'S ALMOST
30 LIGHT-YEARS BEHIND US.

34
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:29,524
ARCHER: ADMIRAL FORREST ASSURES
ME IT'S ONLY A TEMPORARY DETOUR.

35
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:33,028
TUCKER: SOME GEOLOGIC FIREWORKS.
COULD BE FUN.

36
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,529
ARCHER: SET A COURSE.

37
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:36,323
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

38
00:02:52,089 --> 00:02:53,340
[DOOR CHIMES]

39
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:54,633
ARCHER: COME IN.

40
00:02:56,969 --> 00:02:58,470
TRAVIS:
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE, SIR?

41
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,973
ARCHER: SEVERAL, ACTUALLY.

42
00:03:01,015 --> 00:03:02,474
PLEASE.

43
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,434
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

44
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:07,395
TRAVIS: I WAS WONDERING IF
I COULD MAKE A PERSONAL REQUEST.

45
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,272
ARCHER: OF COURSE.

46
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:12,609
TRAVIS: MY FAMILY'S
SHIP, "THE "HORIZON"--

47
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:14,987
WE'RE GOING TO BE
PASSING CLOSE TO IT.

48
00:03:15,029 --> 00:03:16,947
I WOULDN'T MIND
GOING BY FOR A VISIT.

49
00:03:16,989 --> 00:03:19,282
IT'S ABOUT 10 HOURS
OFF OUR FLIGHT PATH.

50
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:22,870
"ENTERPRISE" CAN STILL GET TO
THE PLANET WITH TIME TO SPARE.

51
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:25,706
YOU COULD PICK ME UP
ON THE WAY BACK.

52
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:29,668
ARCHER: I THINK WE CAN MANAGE
WITHOUT YOU FOR A FEW DAYS.

53
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,378
TRAVIS: THANK YOU, SIR.

54
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:34,715
ARCHER: YOUR FOLKS WILL BE
SURPRISED TO SEE YOU.

55
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:36,675
TRAVIS: MY FATHER'S BEEN
ILL FOR A FEW MONTHS.

56
00:03:36,717 --> 00:03:39,011
ARCHER: NOTHING SERIOUS, I HOPE.

57
00:03:39,053 --> 00:03:40,804
TRAVIS:
MY MOTHER SAID HE'LL BE FINE.

58
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:42,931
SHE'S THE SHIP'S MEDIC.

59
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,599
ARCHER: I THOUGHT YOU TOLD ME

60
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:47,352
YOUR MOTHER WAS
THE CHIEF ENGINEER.

61
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:48,979
TRAVIS: SHE'S BOTH.

62
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:52,315
ARCHER: I GUESS THEY HAVE
TO WEAR A LOT OF HATS

63
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,193
TO KEEP THOSE OLD SHIPS RUNNING.

64
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,486
TRAVIS: MY GRANDFATHER
HELD THE RECORD--

65
00:03:56,528 --> 00:03:59,907
5 JOBS AT ONE TIME,
TWO OF THEM ON THE BRIDGE.

66
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,909
ARCHER: THERE WAS A TIME

67
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,954
WHEN I GAVE SERIOUS THOUGHT
TO SERVING ON A CARGO SHIP.

68
00:04:05,996 --> 00:04:09,249
TRAVIS: YOU, SIR?

69
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,710
ARCHER: IT WAS A FEW YEARS
BEFORE STARFLEET WAS CHARTERED.

70
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:13,628
TRAVIS: WHY DIDN'T YOU SIGN UP?

71
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,091
ARCHER: LONG STORY.

72
00:04:17,132 --> 00:04:20,886
I'LL TELL YOU THE NEXT TIME
WE HAVE BREAKFAST.

73
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:23,680
AFTER WE DOCK, I'LL
HAVE PHLOX GO OVER WITH YOU,

74
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:25,682
HAVE HIM TAKE A LOOK
AT YOUR FATHER.

75
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:28,143
TRAVIS:
I'D APPRECIATE THAT, SIR.

76
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,353
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

77
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,361
TUCKER: YOU'LL BE GLAD TO HEAR

78
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:40,030
THE THERMAL SCANNERS
ARE UP AND RUNNING.

79
00:04:40,072 --> 00:04:41,698
T'POL: AND THE IMAGING RELAYS?

80
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:43,951
TUCKER: YEP. WE'LL DROP SIX
OF THEM IN HIGH ORBIT.

81
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:45,744
THAT SHOULD GIVE US
A BIRD'S-EYE VIEW

82
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:48,705
OF EVERY VOLCANO
ON THE PLANET.

83
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:51,875
YOU KNOW, THERE'S NOT GONNA BE
A LOT TO DO ONCE WE GET THERE.

84
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:54,253
SENSORS WILL RECORD
EVERYTHING AUTOMATICALLY.

85
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:56,004
T'POL:
YOU SHOULD HAVE PLENTY OF TIME

86
00:04:56,046 --> 00:05:00,092
TO PRACTICE YOUR HARMONICA.

87
00:05:00,134 --> 00:05:02,719
TUCKER: I'VE TALKED CHEF
INTO DOING SOMETHING SPECIAL.

88
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:06,598
STARTING TUESDAY, IT'S GONNA
BE MOVIE NIGHT EVERY NIGHT.

89
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,433
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE INTERESTED,

90
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:10,144
SEEING HOW YOU ENJOYED
THAT WESTERN.

91
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:11,895
WE'RE GONNA BE SHOWING

92
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:14,231
THE THREE GREATEST
HORROR MOVIES EVER MADE:

93
00:05:14,273 --> 00:05:17,776
"FRANKENSTEIN,"
"BRIDE OF FRANKENSTEIN,"

94
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:19,486
AND "SON OF FRANKENSTEIN."

95
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:22,656
WE MIGHT EVEN THROW IN "ABBOTT
AND COSTELLO MEET FRANKENSTEIN."

96
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:25,951
T'POL: I HAVE NO INTEREST
IN HORROR MOVIES.

97
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:29,704
TUCKER: HOW DO YOU KNOW
IF YOU'VE NEVER SEEN ONE?

98
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:32,291
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO SEE ALL OF THEM.

99
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,209
JUST COME THE FIRST NIGHT.

100
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:37,378
I PROMISE YOU'LL LIKE IT.

101
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:41,800
REANIMATED LIFE-FORMS,
SCIENCE RUN AMOK--

102
00:05:41,842 --> 00:05:43,802
THEY'RE RIGHT UP YOUR ALLEY.

103
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:49,348
REED: FOUR YEARS ISN'T SO LONG.

104
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:54,896
MY LAST FAMILY REUNION
WAS ALMOST A DECADE AGO.

105
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:56,606
TRAVIS:
STARFLEET REALLY OUGHT TO THINK

106
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:58,525
ABOUT PUTTING FAMILIES
ON STARSHIPS.

107
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:00,277
REED: YOU MUST BE JOKING.

108
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:02,487
TRAVIS:
NO ONE WOULD EVER GET HOMESICK.

109
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:04,156
REED: YES.

110
00:06:04,198 --> 00:06:05,991
WELL, THEY'D BETTER
POST A PSYCHOLOGIST ONBOARD,

111
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,617
BECAUSE I'D NEED ONE

112
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,703
IF MY PARENTS WERE
ROAMING THE CORRIDORS.

113
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:12,080
TRAVIS: ON A CARGO SHIP,
YOU CAN'T WALK 10 METERS

114
00:06:12,122 --> 00:06:15,042
WITHOUT RUNNING INTO YOUR
BABYSITTER OR A GREAT-AUNT.

115
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:18,253
HOSHI:
Bridge to Ensign Mayweather.

116
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:21,464
TRAVIS: GO AHEAD.

117
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,382
HOSHI: We've gotten a response
from the "Horizon."

118
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:25,344
It's your mother.

119
00:06:25,384 --> 00:06:27,262
TRAVIS: THANKS, HOSHI.
PUT IT THROUGH TO MY QUARTERS.

120
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:35,145
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S PERSONAL LOG,
JANUARY 10, 2153.

121
00:06:35,187 --> 00:06:38,315
WE'RE ON COURSE FOR OUR
RENDEZVOUS WITH THE "HORIZON."

122
00:06:38,357 --> 00:06:40,650
UNFORTUNATELY,
I'VE JUST RECEIVED WORD

123
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:42,236
THAT ENSIGN MAYWEATHER'S FAMILY

124
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,654
IS FACING
AN UNEXPECTED TRAGEDY.

125
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:50,451
MIND IF I JOIN YOU?

126
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:52,871
TRAVIS: OF COURSE NOT.

127
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:00,379
ARCHER: I HAVEN'T BEEN UP HERE
SINCE WE LAUNCHED.

128
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:15,602
COME HERE A LOT?

129
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:18,146
TRAVIS: EVERY NOW AND THEN.

130
00:07:20,732 --> 00:07:24,069
ARCHER: COMMANDER TUCKER
TOLD ME WHAT HAPPENED.

131
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:26,238
I'M SORRY.

132
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:30,951
TRAVIS: MY MOTHER SENT
A MESSAGE TO STARFLEET

133
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:33,620
SIX WEEKS AGO.

134
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:36,039
BUT I NEVER GOT IT.

135
00:07:40,752 --> 00:07:46,258
ARCHER: THE CIVILIAN CHANNELS
CAN BE PRETTY SLOW.

136
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:49,386
TRAVIS:
I SHOULD HAVE CALLED HIM.

137
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:54,682
WE WERE IN COMM RANGE
A FEW MONTHS AGO.

138
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:59,562
I GUESS I WASN'T READY
TO TALK TO HIM YET.

139
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:04,901
HE WASN'T VERY HAPPY WITH ME
WHEN I JOINED STARFLEET.

140
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:07,862
HE'D BEEN GROOMING ME
FOR HIS JOB...

141
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:11,616
SINCE I WAS A KID.

142
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:13,868
ARCHER: I'M SURE.

143
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:19,082
IT WASN'T EASY FOR HIM
WHEN YOU LEFT.

144
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:23,795
BUT I KNOW FOR A FACT...

145
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:25,880
THAT HE WAS PROUD OF YOU.

146
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:32,887
TRAVIS:
WITH ALL RESPECT, SIR...

147
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:37,767
I'M NOT SO SURE HE WAS.

148
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:43,564
ARCHER: DID HE EVER TELL YOU
ABOUT THE LETTER HE SENT ME?

149
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:49,696
IT WAS ALMOST 2 1/2 YEARS AGO.

150
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:53,700
THERE WERE A FEW CANDIDATES I
WAS LOOKING AT FOR HELM OFFICER.

151
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:57,787
I WAS HAVING
A LITTLE TROUBLE DECIDING,

152
00:08:57,829 --> 00:09:00,999
SO I CONTACTED
THEIR FORMER C.O.s,

153
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,793
HOPING FOR
A MORE PERSONAL EVALUATION.

154
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:06,380
TRAVIS: WHAT DID HE SAY?

155
00:09:06,421 --> 00:09:09,716
ARCHER: HE WROTE
THE SHORTEST RECOMMENDATION--

156
00:09:09,757 --> 00:09:11,885
JUST ONE SENTENCE.

157
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:15,555
HE SAID...

158
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:19,267
HE'D NEVER MET A MORE
NATURAL STICK-AND-RUDDER MAN

159
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,144
IN HIS LIFE,

160
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:25,357
AND I'D BE A FOOL
IF I DIDN'T CHOOSE YOU.

161
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:32,531
WHEN I SAW HOW YOU HANDLED
YOURSELF AT THE HELM...

162
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:37,327
I KNEW HE WAS RIGHT.

163
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:39,538
TRAVIS: I WISH...

164
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:45,377
HE WOULD HAVE TOLD ME THAT.

165
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,217
PHLOX: AS I SUSPECTED.

166
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:53,801
IT'S NOTHING MORE
THAN A SIMPLE HEADACHE.

167
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:55,678
T'POL: I WAS HOPING
FOR SOMETHING MORE SERIOUS.

168
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,514
PHLOX: OH?

169
00:09:57,556 --> 00:10:00,100
T'POL: I'VE BEEN COERCED
INTO WATCHING TONIGHT'S MOVIE.

170
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:02,227
PHLOX: AH, IF YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR A MEDICAL EXCUSE,

171
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:03,978
I'M AFRAID YOU'RE OUT OF LUCK.

172
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,189
IF IT'S ANY CONSOLATION,
I'LL BE THERE AS WELL.

173
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:08,108
I AGREE THIS FORM OF
ENTERTAINMENT IS RATHER CRUDE,

174
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:09,609
BUT IT CAN OFTEN PROVIDE

175
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,152
AN ENLIGHTENING GLIMPSE
INTO HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

176
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:13,154
T'POL: DON'T BE SURPRISED

177
00:10:13,196 --> 00:10:15,907
IF YOU SEE ME
HERE AGAIN AFTERWARDS.

178
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:19,035
I HAVE LITTLE DOUBT
MY HEADACHE WILL RETURN.

179
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,834
TUCKER: JUST A QUICK TOUR
OF THE ENGINE ROOM,

180
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,253
THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.

181
00:10:28,295 --> 00:10:30,213
THE "HORIZON'S" 50 YEARS OLD.

182
00:10:30,255 --> 00:10:32,882
I'M SURE YOU'VE SEEN FAR
MORE IMPRESSIVE WARP REACTORS.

183
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:35,718
TUCKER: ZEFRAM COCHRANE DESIGNED
THAT ENGINE HIMSELF.

184
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,887
I'VE HEARD RUMORS
THAT HE PERSONALLY SIGNED

185
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:40,890
THE INSIDE
OF EACH REACTOR CASING.

186
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:44,936
OH, UH...ALMOST FORGOT.

187
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:47,981
TRAVIS: WHAT'S THIS?
TUCKER: A FEW FAMILY PHOTOS.

188
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:51,651
I DOWNLOADED EVERY PICTURE I'VE
TAKEN SINCE WE LEFT SPACEDOCK.

189
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:55,238
THOUGHT YOUR MOM MIGHT LIKE TO
SEE WHAT HER BOY'S BEEN UP TO.

190
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,365
TRAVIS: THANK YOU, SIR.
TUCKER: YOU BET.

191
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:22,681
TRAVIS: I WOULDN'T CALL IT
A DANGEROUS MISSION.

192
00:11:22,723 --> 00:11:24,267
WE'VE GOTTEN INTO
A FEW SKIRMISHES,

193
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,935
BUT NOTHING
WE COULDN'T HANDLE.

194
00:11:25,977 --> 00:11:28,313
RIANNA: I GOT A LETTER
FROM YOUR SISTER.

195
00:11:28,355 --> 00:11:30,231
SHE SAID YOU MENTIONED
A CLOSE CALL

196
00:11:30,273 --> 00:11:32,150
WITH SOME KIND OF STORM.

197
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:35,320
TRAVIS: WE RAN INTO A SMALL
WAVE FRONT A FEW MONTHS AGO.

198
00:11:35,362 --> 00:11:37,238
THE CREW HAD TO SQUEEZE
INTO ONE OF THE NACELLES

199
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,948
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.

200
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:41,742
SHE PROBABLY MADE IT
SOUND WORSE THAN IT WAS.

201
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,620
RIANNA:
SHE ALSO MENTIONED SOMETHING

202
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:46,747
ABOUT ALIEN SOLDIERS
FORCING THEIR WAY ABOARD.

203
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:49,292
TRAVIS: IT WAS REALLY JUST
A MISUNDERSTANDING.

204
00:11:49,334 --> 00:11:52,212
THEY THOUGHT "ENTERPRISE"
HAD BEEN ABANDONED.

205
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:54,506
CAPTAIN ARCHER CONVINCED THEM
TO LEAVE.

206
00:11:54,548 --> 00:11:57,884
RIANNA: I GUESS THERE'S
NO POINT IN ASKING YOU

207
00:11:57,925 --> 00:11:59,927
ABOUT THE ROMULAN MINEFIELD.

208
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,804
TRAVIS: HOW'D YOU KNOW
ABOUT THAT?

209
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:05,016
RIANNA: I'VE BEEN SERVING
ON CARGO SHIPS FOR A LONG TIME.

210
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,685
I'VE MADE A FEW CONTACTS
HERE AND THERE.

211
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:07,894
[ALARM]

212
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:11,231
CREWMAN: Stand by to go to warp.

213
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:13,149
[RUMBLING]

214
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,990
TRAVIS:
CHARLIE MUST BE AT THE HELM.

215
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:22,576
RIANNA: WHAT MAKES YOU SAY THAT?

216
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:25,328
TRAVIS: HIS WARP JUMPS
WERE ALWAYS A LITTLE ROUGH.

217
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:26,829
[RIANNA LAUGHS]

218
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:28,582
TRAVIS: WHERE ARE WE HEADED?

219
00:12:28,623 --> 00:12:31,292
RIANNA: DENEVA STATION. JUST
A QUICK RUN TO PICK UP SUPPLIES.

220
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:33,211
WE'LL HAVE YOU BACK
IN PLENTY OF TIME.

221
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:35,004
WELDER: WATCH YOUR STEP, MA'AM.

222
00:12:35,046 --> 00:12:37,716
WELDER: TRAVIS?
TRAVIS: HEY!

223
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:39,593
WELDER:
HAVEN'T SEEN YOU FOR A WHILE.

224
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:41,511
DID YOU LOCK YOURSELF IN
A CARGO CONTAINER AGAIN?

225
00:12:41,553 --> 00:12:45,181
TRAVIS: DO YOU ALWAYS HAVE
TO BRING THAT UP?

226
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:47,850
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

227
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:49,852
HEY. IF YOU'RE NOT BUSY TONIGHT,
STOP BY THE MESS.

228
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:51,938
TRAVIS: I WILL.

229
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:58,903
RIANNA: DID YOU FORGET YOUR WAY?

230
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:00,655
TRAVIS: GUEST QUARTERS
ARE OVER HERE.

231
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:03,074
RIANNA: YOU'RE NOT ASSIGNED
TO GUEST QUARTERS.

232
00:13:10,749 --> 00:13:13,334
TRAVIS: I THOUGHT MY ROOM
HAD BEEN REASSIGNED.

233
00:13:13,376 --> 00:13:15,211
RIANNA:
IT WAS, BUT THEY DIDN'T MIND

234
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:16,755
GIVING IT UP FOR A FEW DAYS.

235
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:19,048
WE DON'T GET V.I.P.s VERY OFTEN.

236
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,052
I FOUND SOME
OF YOUR OLD THINGS.

237
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:25,179
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
FEEL MORE AT HOME.

238
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,183
TRAVIS: I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU KEPT THIS.

239
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:34,147
RIANNA: YOU STAYED UP
ALL NIGHT FOR A MONTH,

240
00:13:34,188 --> 00:13:35,774
MAPPING EVERY SYSTEM

241
00:13:35,814 --> 00:13:38,359
YOU PLANNED TO VISIT
WHEN YOU GREW UP.

242
00:13:38,401 --> 00:13:41,404
TRAVIS:
I'VE STILL GOT A WAYS TO GO.

243
00:13:43,281 --> 00:13:45,784
RIANNA: I'M GLAD YOU'RE HOME.

244
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,537
TRAVIS: ME, TOO.

245
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:54,542
WE'RE GOING TO GET
THROUGH THIS, MOM.

246
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:02,342
[RIANNA SIGHS]

247
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,469
THOSE, UH, PLASMA INJECTORS

248
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:06,929
AREN'T GOING TO ALIGN
THEMSELVES.

249
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,931
I SHOULD GO.

250
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,685
OH, AFTER YOU'VE SETTLED IN,
UH, COME BY THE ENGINE ROOM.

251
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:13,978
SOME PEOPLE WANT TO SAY HELLO.

252
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:35,750
PAUL: TRANSFER THESE
CANISTERS OVER TO MODULE 4.

253
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:37,502
CREWMAN: MM-HMM.

254
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:40,046
TRAVIS: ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OLD
ENOUGH TO DRIVE THAT THING?

255
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:43,966
PAUL: AN ENSIGN OUGHT TO SALUTE

256
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:45,719
BEFORE ADDRESSING A CAPTAIN.

257
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,220
TRAVIS: ACTING CAPTAIN.

258
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:49,889
DON'T LET IT GO TO YOUR HEAD.

259
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:53,351
PAUL: I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU
IN A FEW MINUTES.

260
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:05,488
TRAVIS:
THE JACKET LOOKS GOOD ON YOU.

261
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:08,074
PAUL: THANKS.

262
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:11,285
DIDN'T THINK I'D BE
WEARING IT THIS SOON.

263
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:17,417
TRAVIS: BUSINESS MUST BE GOOD.

264
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:20,378
I'VE NEVER SEEN
THIS MODULE SO FULL.

265
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,422
PAUL:
THE BIGGEST PROBLEM THESE DAYS

266
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,382
IS KEEPING TRACK OF EVERYTHING.

267
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:27,260
DAD KEPT A LOT OF
THE INVENTORY IN HIS HEAD.

268
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:29,721
I'M TRYING TO RECONSTRUCT
THE DATABASE.

269
00:15:29,763 --> 00:15:33,140
WE STILL CAN'T FIND
THE STROMATOPOD LARVAE

270
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:36,018
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE DELIVERING
TO THE DEMERIANS.

271
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,397
I ONLY HOPE IT DIDN'T END UP
IN COLD STORAGE.

272
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:40,857
TRAVIS: IF YOU NEED
ME TO HELP OUT WITH ANYTHING--

273
00:15:40,899 --> 00:15:44,485
PAUL:
THANKS, BUT WE CAN HANDLE IT.

274
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:49,574
YOU'RE ON LEAVE.
I'M NOT GONNA PUT YOU TO WORK.

275
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:53,536
TRAVIS: SEE YOU AT DINNER?

276
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:00,167
PAUL: TRAVIS.

277
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:02,002
YOU MIGHT WANT TO CHANGE

278
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:04,088
INTO SOMETHING
A LITTLE LESS CONSPICUOUS.

279
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,737
T'POL: I'VE DEPLOYED
THE IMAGING RELAYS.

280
00:16:27,779 --> 00:16:30,114
ARCHER: HOW LONG UNTIL
THE SHOW BEGINS?

281
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:32,241
T'POL: APPROXIMATELY 30 HOURS.

282
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:35,411
THE HOLOMETRIC CAMERA
STILL NEEDS TO BE CALIBRATED.

283
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:38,581
TUCKER: I CAN HELP WITH THAT.
ARCHER: GET STARTED.

284
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:42,001
I'D LIKE TO SHARE OUR PICTURES
WITH STARFLEET,

285
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:44,671
GIVE ADMIRAL FORREST
A FRONT-ROW SEAT.

286
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:46,798
HOSHI: ECHO III's WITHIN RANGE.

287
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:49,175
IT SHOULDN'T BE TOO HARD
TO SET UP A DOWNLINK.

288
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:54,430
TUCKER: SO YOU COMING TONIGHT?

289
00:16:54,472 --> 00:16:56,307
T'POL: IF THESE SENSORS
ARE CALIBRATED BY THEN.

290
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:58,893
TUCKER: WELL, YOU BETTER
MAKE UP YOUR MIND.

291
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:02,229
SEATS ARE GONNA FILL UP FAST.

292
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,565
T'POL:
ACCORDING TO THE DATABASE,

293
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:07,443
"FRANKENSTEIN" IS ALSO
A WORK OF LITERATURE.

294
00:17:07,485 --> 00:17:09,236
TUCKER: MARY SHELLEY WROTE IT,

295
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:11,030
THE WIFE OF A FAMOUS POET.

296
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,740
T'POL:
PERHAPS A DRAMATIC READING

297
00:17:12,782 --> 00:17:15,075
WOULD BE MORE ILLUMINATING.

298
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,036
TUCKER: YOU EXPECT A MESS HALL
FULL OF CREWMEN

299
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:19,580
TO SIT STILL WHILE SOMEONE
READS TO THEM?

300
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,582
T'POL: THEY'D BE MORE LIKELY

301
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:25,127
TO APPRECIATE THE AUTHOR'S
TRUE INTENT.

302
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:28,756
TUCKER: YOU WANT TO START
A BOOK CLUB, GO RIGHT AHEAD.

303
00:17:28,798 --> 00:17:32,092
YOU'RE GONNA BE THERE
TONIGHT, AREN'T YOU, SIR?

304
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:34,136
ARCHER: WOULDN'T MISS IT.

305
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:37,557
TUCKER: WELL, I'LL SAVE YOU
SOME POPCORN.

306
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:45,565
ARCHER: MIGHT BE A GOOD IDEA
FOR YOU TO GO, TOO.

307
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:47,274
IT MIGHT BE FUN,

308
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:50,152
AND A LITTLE FRATERNIZING
COULDN'T HURT.

309
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:55,199
T'POL: I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW SITTING SILENTLY

310
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:58,452
IN A DARKENED ROOM
CONSTITUTES FRATERNIZING.

311
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:03,332
ARCHER:
IT'S A COMMUNAL EXPERIENCE.

312
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:07,127
TELL YOU WHAT.

313
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:09,171
LET'S MAKE A NIGHT OF IT--

314
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:12,759
DINNER IN THE CAPTAIN'S MESS,
1800, MOVIE AT 1930.

315
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,385
YOU'LL BE MY DATE.

316
00:18:14,427 --> 00:18:15,929
T'POL: I BEG YOUR PARDON.

317
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:17,430
ARCHER:
I'LL BE A PERFECT GENTLEMAN.

318
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:20,307
AND IF YOU DON'T
LIKE THE MOVIE,

319
00:18:20,349 --> 00:18:23,269
I'LL NEVER ASK YOU TO SIT
THROUGH ANOTHER ONE.

320
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:38,659
TRAVIS: ALL RIGHT.

321
00:18:38,701 --> 00:18:40,995
TRY IT NOW.

322
00:18:43,456 --> 00:18:44,624
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

323
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,542
NICHOLS: MM-HMM.

324
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:48,711
TRAVIS: I'VE INCREASED THE RANGE
OF THE NAVIGATION SENSORS.

325
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:51,672
THE HELM WILL MAKE COURSE
CORRECTIONS A LOT QUICKER.

326
00:18:54,216 --> 00:18:56,052
PAUL: WHAT'S WRONG?

327
00:18:56,094 --> 00:18:59,138
TRAVIS: I'M JUST WORKING
ON A FEW UPGRADES.

328
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:03,601
PAUL: I DON'T REMEMBER ASKING
FOR ANY UPGRADES.

329
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,395
TRAVIS: YOU WERE BUSY.
I DIDN'T WANT TO BOTHER YOU.

330
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,272
YOU'RE GOING TO LOVE THIS.

331
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:11,191
YOU KNOW THOSE PORT STABILIZERS
THAT WERE ALWAYS ACTING UP?

332
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,736
BEFORE I LEFT, I SPOKE
WITH COMMANDER TUCKER.

333
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:15,571
PAUL: COMMANDER TUCKER?

334
00:19:15,613 --> 00:19:17,281
TRAVIS: OUR CHIEF ENGINEER
ON "ENTERPRISE."

335
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:20,827
HE SHOWED ME HOW TO RECONFIGURE
THE SPATIAL DISCRIMINATORS.

336
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:22,954
THEY SHOULDN'T GIVE YOU
ANY MORE TROUBLE.

337
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:27,125
PAUL: WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN

338
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,961
IF THESE IMPROVEMENTS OF YOURS
GO OFFLINE?

339
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:33,631
YOU'LL BE BACK ON YOUR STARFLEET
SHIP, OUT OF COMM RANGE.

340
00:19:33,673 --> 00:19:35,299
WHO'S GONNA FIX IT?

341
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:39,887
I'D PREFER IT IF YOU DIDN'T
MODIFY ANY MORE SYSTEMS

342
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:42,807
WITHOUT DISCUSSING IT WITH ME.

343
00:19:42,849 --> 00:19:45,852
TRAVIS: WHATEVER YOU SAY...SIR.

344
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:50,272
PAUL: MAYBE YOU CAN STOP
BY ENGINEERING...

345
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:54,401
BUILD US A WARP 5 ENGINE.

346
00:20:10,501 --> 00:20:11,878
[DOOR BUZZES]

347
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:14,380
TRAVIS: COME IN.

348
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,799
NORA: I HEARD WE HAD A VISITOR.

349
00:20:16,841 --> 00:20:19,135
TRAVIS: WORD TRAVELS FAST.

350
00:20:19,177 --> 00:20:21,804
[NORA LAUGHING]

351
00:20:24,098 --> 00:20:26,726
NORA: I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE
HE'S GONE.

352
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,020
I'M SO SORRY, TRAVIS.

353
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:31,064
TRAVIS: THANKS.

354
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,568
NORA: AREN'T YOU A LITTLE OLD
FOR THIS?

355
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:37,653
TRAVIS: I DON'T KNOW.

356
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:40,031
I THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE FUN
TO REGRESS FOR A WHILE.

357
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:41,699
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE TURN OFF
THE GRAV PLATING

358
00:20:41,741 --> 00:20:43,201
AND JUMP ON THE BED?

359
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,619
NORA: AND GET GROUNDED AGAIN?

360
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:48,414
THAT WOULDN'T LOOK TOO GOOD
ON YOUR STARFLEET RECORD.

361
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:50,332
[LAUGHTER]

362
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:52,501
HOW'S "ENTERPRISE"?

363
00:20:52,543 --> 00:20:54,087
TRAVIS: KEEPS US BUSY.

364
00:20:54,128 --> 00:20:56,338
WE'VE GONE 150 LIGHT-YEARS,

365
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:59,133
SEEN 22 INHABITED WORLDS.

366
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:00,801
NORA: IN 18 MONTHS?

367
00:21:00,843 --> 00:21:02,970
TRAVIS: YOU CAN'T BELIEVE
WHAT'S OUT THERE.

368
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:05,973
NORA: COLUMBUS, MAGELLAN,
TRAVIS MAYWEATHER.

369
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:07,558
[NORA LAUGHING]

370
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,560
HOW LONG ARE YOU HOME FOR?

371
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,353
TRAVIS: JUST A FEW DAYS.

372
00:21:11,395 --> 00:21:13,522
NORA: ANY CHANCE OF GETTING
AN EXTENDED LEAVE?

373
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:15,524
TRAVIS: I'M AFRAID NOT.

374
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:18,444
I DOUBT MAGELLAN GOT
MUCH TIME OFF, EITHER.

375
00:21:21,864 --> 00:21:24,825
WHAT'S WRONG?

376
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:28,370
NORA: I DON'T MEAN TO SPOIL
YOUR VISIT, BUT...

377
00:21:28,412 --> 00:21:30,873
THINGS HAVEN'T EXACTLY
BEEN RUNNING LIKE CLOCKWORK

378
00:21:30,915 --> 00:21:32,666
SINCE YOUR FATHER DIED.

379
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:34,252
TRAVIS: WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

380
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:36,378
NORA: WE MISSED A RENDEZVOUS

381
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,297
WITH AN ORION FREIGHTER
2 WEEKS AGO.

382
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:40,549
THE CARGO AUTHORITY
WASN'T TOO PLEASED.

383
00:21:40,591 --> 00:21:42,509
WE'RE ALSO LOW ON DEUTERIUM.

384
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:46,222
WE'VE HAD TO DIP INTO
THE RESERVES TWICE THIS MONTH.

385
00:21:46,264 --> 00:21:48,599
MORALE'S BEEN BETTER, TRAVIS.

386
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:51,185
"HORIZON'S" LOST ITS CAPTAIN,

387
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:54,897
AND SOME OF THE CREW
ARE STARTING TO WONDER

388
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:57,066
IF PAUL'S READY FOR THE JOB.

389
00:21:57,108 --> 00:22:01,570
YOU MIGHT HAVE NOTICED
HE'S BEEN A LITTLE ON EDGE.

390
00:22:01,612 --> 00:22:04,073
TRAVIS: HE'S ALWAYS ON EDGE.

391
00:22:04,115 --> 00:22:06,951
NORA: MORE THAN USUAL.

392
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:09,745
TRAVIS: MY MOTHER HASN'T
MENTIONED ANY OF THIS.

393
00:22:09,787 --> 00:22:11,998
NORA: I GUESS SHE DIDN'T
WANT TO WORRY YOU.

394
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,211
TRAVIS: HE'S ONLY BEEN
IN COMMAND A FEW WEEKS.

395
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:18,796
GIVE HIM A CHANCE.

396
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,589
HE'LL GROW INTO IT.

397
00:22:20,631 --> 00:22:22,758
NORA: I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

398
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:24,844
I'M SURE THIS IS THE LAST THING
YOU WANTED TO HEAR RIGHT NOW.

399
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:26,512
I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD KNOW.

400
00:22:26,553 --> 00:22:28,055
TRAVIS: THANKS.

401
00:22:28,097 --> 00:22:29,515
[RUMBLING]

402
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:31,517
CHARLIE AT THE HELM?

403
00:22:31,558 --> 00:22:33,144
NORA: JUST A LITTLE
SPATIAL TURBULENCE.

404
00:22:33,186 --> 00:22:35,353
YOU'VE GOTTEN SPOILED
ON "ENTERPRISE."

405
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:39,192
[WEAPON FIRING]

406
00:22:39,233 --> 00:22:41,777
TRAVIS: THAT'S NO TURBULENCE.

407
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:53,289
NICHOLS:
HULL FRACTURE IN MODULE 3.

408
00:22:53,331 --> 00:22:54,915
WE'RE VENTING ATMOSPHERE.

409
00:22:54,957 --> 00:22:57,626
PAUL: SEAL IT OFF.
TRY HAILING THEM AGAIN.

410
00:22:57,668 --> 00:23:00,546
NICHOLS:
THEY'RE STILL NOT RESPONDING.

411
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:02,965
TRAVIS: WHAT'S GOING ON?
PAUL: WE'RE UNDER ATTACK.

412
00:23:03,007 --> 00:23:05,092
TRAVIS: BY WHO?
PAUL: I DON'T KNOW.

413
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:07,928
NICHOLS: SHOULD I ARM
THE PLASMA TURRETS?

414
00:23:07,970 --> 00:23:09,847
PAUL: NO.

415
00:23:09,889 --> 00:23:13,851
TRANSFER RESERVE POWER
TO THE HULL PLATING.

416
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:16,062
WE NEED TO GET OUT OF
THEIR WEAPONS RANGE.

417
00:23:16,103 --> 00:23:17,646
GO TO MAXIMUM WARP.

418
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:20,440
TRAVIS: YOU'RE HAULING
30,000 METRIC TONS.

419
00:23:20,482 --> 00:23:21,859
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO BE
ABLE TO OUTRUN THEM.

420
00:23:21,901 --> 00:23:24,904
PAUL: YOU HEARD ME.
NICHOLS: YES, SIR.

421
00:23:26,572 --> 00:23:28,157
WARP 1.6.

422
00:23:28,199 --> 00:23:31,577
1.7.

423
00:23:31,618 --> 00:23:34,580
WARP 1.8.

424
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:37,457
TRAVIS: THEY'RE STILL CLOSING.
PAUL: A LITTLE MORE.

425
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:39,252
NICHOLS: 1.85.

426
00:23:46,842 --> 00:23:48,969
THEY'RE MOVING OFF.

427
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:51,222
PAUL: REDUCE SPEED TO 1.5.

428
00:23:55,059 --> 00:23:57,519
TRAVIS: THEY ATTACHED SOMETHING
TO THE HULL.

429
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:59,397
PAUL: SHOW ME.

430
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:05,027
NICHOLS: IT'S EMITTING
A SUBSPACE SIGNAL.

431
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:07,738
COULD BE SOME KIND OF BEACON.

432
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:09,282
PAUL: CALL ENGINEERING.

433
00:24:09,323 --> 00:24:11,284
TELL THEM TO GET SOMEONE
OUT THERE TO PRY IT OFF.

434
00:24:11,325 --> 00:24:13,244
TRAVIS: I WOULDN'T
RECOMMEND THAT.

435
00:24:14,661 --> 00:24:17,957
THIS IS A DICOBALT SIGNATURE--

436
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:20,584
A HIGH-YIELD EXPLOSIVE.

437
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:23,879
IF ANYONE GETS TOO CLOSE,
IT MIGHT DECIDE TO GO OFF.

438
00:24:28,759 --> 00:24:30,803
NICHOLS: THE "CONSTELLATION"
SENT US THIS.

439
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:32,805
THIS SHIP ATTACKED THEM
EIGHT WEEKS AGO,

440
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:34,723
AND IT PLANTED A BEACON
ON THEIR HULL.

441
00:24:34,765 --> 00:24:36,309
A DAY LATER,

442
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,352
THIS CRUISER SHOWED UP
AND DEMANDED THEIR CARGO.

443
00:24:38,394 --> 00:24:40,396
THE "CONSTELLATION" TRIED
TO DRIVE THEM OFF,

444
00:24:40,438 --> 00:24:42,440
BUT THE ALIENS GOT ABOARD
AND KILLED THREE OF THEIR CREW.

445
00:24:42,522 --> 00:24:44,650
THEN THEY TOOK
THE ENTIRE SHIPMENT.

446
00:24:44,691 --> 00:24:47,236
TRAVIS: WHAT KIND OF WEAPONS
DOES THE "CONSTELLATION" HAVE?

447
00:24:47,278 --> 00:24:50,990
NICHOLS: TWO PLASMA TURRETS,
SAME AS US.

448
00:24:54,534 --> 00:24:57,955
PAUL: THERE HAS TO BE A WAY
TO REMOVE THAT BEACON.

449
00:24:57,997 --> 00:25:00,082
RIANNA: I WOULDN'T RISK IT.

450
00:25:01,459 --> 00:25:04,544
IF IT DETONATES,
YOU COULD LOSE THE NACELLE.

451
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:10,176
PAUL: IF WE JETTISON
A FEW TONS OF THAT ORE,

452
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,760
CAN WE INCREASE TO WARP 2?

453
00:25:11,802 --> 00:25:13,595
RIANNA: I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

454
00:25:13,637 --> 00:25:15,181
PAUL: THAT SHOULD ALLOW US

455
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:17,308
TO REACH DENEVA STATION
AHEAD OF SCHEDULE.

456
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:19,643
IT'S WELL-ARMED.
WE SHOULD BE SAFE THERE.

457
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:22,313
TRAVIS: WHAT HAPPENS IF THEY
COME BACK BEFORE WE ARRIVE?

458
00:25:22,355 --> 00:25:23,856
PAUL: THERE'S NO OTHER CHOICE.

459
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,192
WE CAN'T SHOOT OUR WAY
OUT OF THIS.

460
00:25:29,403 --> 00:25:31,780
TRAVIS: I'VE SEEN THIS KIND
OF ENGINE CONFIGURATION BEFORE.

461
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:34,908
IT'S NOT THAT DIFFERENT
FROM A MAZARITE SHIP.

462
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:36,702
RIANNA: MAZARITE?

463
00:25:36,743 --> 00:25:39,372
TRAVIS: WE HAD
SOME TROUBLE WITH THEM.

464
00:25:39,413 --> 00:25:40,956
WE MANAGED TO KNOCK OUT
THEIR ENGINES

465
00:25:40,998 --> 00:25:42,540
WITH OUR PHASE CANNONS.

466
00:25:42,582 --> 00:25:45,585
PAUL:
WE DON'T HAVE PHASE CANNONS.

467
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:47,545
TRAVIS:
I CAN TIE THE PLASMA TURRETS

468
00:25:47,587 --> 00:25:49,423
DIRECTLY INTO
THE IMPULSE ENGINES.

469
00:25:49,465 --> 00:25:51,050
LIEUTENANT REED DID THAT,

470
00:25:51,091 --> 00:25:53,135
AND IT INCREASED
OUR YIELD BY 80%.

471
00:25:53,177 --> 00:25:54,887
PAUL: I'M NOT GONNA RISK
ALL OF OUR LIVES

472
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:57,597
BY GETTING INTO A FIGHT
WE CAN'T WIN.

473
00:25:59,725 --> 00:26:03,479
IF THEY REACH US BEFORE
WE MAKE IT TO DENEVA,

474
00:26:03,521 --> 00:26:05,272
WE'LL GIVE THEM
WHAT THEY WANT.

475
00:26:05,314 --> 00:26:06,899
TRAVIS: IF THERE'S ONE THING

476
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,734
I'VE LEARNED
FROM CAPTAIN ARCHER,

477
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:10,777
IT'S THAT YOU DON'T GIVE IN
TO PEOPLE LIKE THIS.

478
00:26:10,819 --> 00:26:13,030
YOU'RE ONLY GOING TO
ENCOURAGE MORE ATTACKS,

479
00:26:13,072 --> 00:26:16,200
NOT JUST AGAINST YOU
BUT OTHER CARGO SHIPS.

480
00:26:16,242 --> 00:26:19,495
PAUL: I APPRECIATE THE ADVICE,
BUT THIS ISN'T YOUR PROBLEM.

481
00:26:19,537 --> 00:26:22,164
YOU'RE NOT PART
OF THIS CREW ANYMORE.

482
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:26,126
JETTISON THAT ORE
AND INCREASE OUR SPEED.

483
00:26:29,463 --> 00:26:32,966
RIANNA: EVEN YOUR FATHER
HAD TO MAKE COMPROMISES.

484
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:36,970
THE SAFEST THING TO DO
IS GIVE THEM WHAT THEY WANT.

485
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:40,182
CARGO CAN BE REPLACED.

486
00:26:49,649 --> 00:26:50,984
DOCTOR FRANKENSTEIN:<i> FOOL.</i>

487
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:52,652
<i>IF THIS STORM DEVELOPS</i>
<i>AS I HOPE,</i>

488
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:54,488
<i>YOU WILL HAVE PLENTY</i>
<i>TO BE AFRAID OF</i>

489
00:26:54,530 --> 00:26:56,740
<i>BEFORE THE NIGHT'S OVER.</i>

490
00:26:56,782 --> 00:26:59,743
<i>GO ON. FIX THE ELECTRODES.</i>

491
00:26:59,785 --> 00:27:02,037
<i>THIS STORM WILL BE MAGNIFICENT.</i>

492
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:05,165
<i>ALL THE ELECTRICAL SECRETS</i>
<i>OF HEAVEN.</i>

493
00:27:05,207 --> 00:27:07,793
<i>THIS TIME WE'RE READY.</i>
<i>EH, FRITZ?</i>

494
00:27:07,834 --> 00:27:09,545
<i>READY.</i>

495
00:27:09,587 --> 00:27:10,796
<i>[THUNDER]</i>

496
00:27:10,837 --> 00:27:12,672
ARCHER: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

497
00:27:12,714 --> 00:27:15,759
T'POL: REVIEWING THIS MORNING'S
SENSOR DATA.

498
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:18,720
ARCHER: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GONNA GIVE THIS A CHANCE.

499
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:21,765
DR. FRANKENSTEIN:
<i>JUST A FEW STITCHES.</i>

500
00:27:21,807 --> 00:27:25,603
<i>LOOK, HERE'S</i>
<i>THE FINAL TOUCH--</i>

501
00:27:25,643 --> 00:27:26,979
<i>A BRAIN YOU STOLE, FRITZ.</i>

502
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:29,022
FRITZ:<i> YES.</i>

503
00:27:29,064 --> 00:27:31,108
FRANKENSTEIN:<i> THINK OF IT--</i>
<i>THE BRAIN OF A DEAD MAN...</i>

504
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:33,486
PHLOX: THIS DR. FRANKENSTEIN--
HIS TECHNIQUE IS NOT DISSIMILAR

505
00:27:33,527 --> 00:27:35,946
TO A PRACTICE ON B'SAARI II.

506
00:27:35,988 --> 00:27:37,906
THEY SUCCESSFULLY USED
AN ISOLYTIC CURRENT

507
00:27:37,948 --> 00:27:40,159
TO REANIMATE THE BODIES
OF THE RECENTLY DECEASED.

508
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,286
TUCKER: REALLY?
PHLOX: MM-HMM.

509
00:27:42,328 --> 00:27:44,371
OF COURSE,
THE REVIVED INDIVIDUALS

510
00:27:44,413 --> 00:27:46,664
WEREN'T CAPABLE OF MORE
THAN BASIC CELLULAR METABOLISM.

511
00:27:46,706 --> 00:27:49,126
HOWEVER, THE B'SAARI
HAVE DEVELOPED A PROCEDURE

512
00:27:49,168 --> 00:27:51,878
THAT, UH, SHOWS PROMISE
IN REPAIRING THE SYNAPTIC, UH...

513
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,464
T'POL: WE CAN STOP THE FILM

514
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:55,841
IF IT'S DISTURBING
YOUR CONVERSATION.

515
00:27:57,968 --> 00:28:00,720
[PHLOX CLEARS THROAT]

516
00:28:00,762 --> 00:28:03,349
<i>[THUNDER]</i>

517
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:04,891
DR. FRANKENSTEIN:
<i>IN 15 MINUTES, THE STORM</i>

518
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:06,726
<i>SHOULD BE AT ITS HEIGHT.</i>

519
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:09,062
<i>THEN WE'LL BE READY.</i>

520
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:11,524
<i>WHAT'S THAT NOISE?</i>

521
00:28:11,565 --> 00:28:13,233
<i>[TAPPING]</i>

522
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:19,657
NICHOLS: CAPTAIN?

523
00:28:19,697 --> 00:28:22,409
LOOKS LIKE SOMEONE'S REROUTING
THE IMPULSE RELAYS.

524
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:25,120
PAUL: WHERE?

525
00:28:25,162 --> 00:28:28,081
NICHOLS: MODULE 5.
PAUL: YOU HAVE THE BRIDGE.

526
00:28:38,258 --> 00:28:39,926
I THOUGHT I MADE MYSELF CLEAR.

527
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:43,639
TRAVIS: IF THOSE ALIENS
COME BACK, YOU'LL THANK ME.

528
00:28:43,681 --> 00:28:46,559
PAUL: I TOLD YOU, I'M NOT GOING
TO TAKE THIS SHIP INTO BATTLE.

529
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:47,976
TRAVIS: YOU MAY NOT
HAVE A CHOICE.

530
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:49,853
PAUL: I DIDN'T ASK
FOR YOUR OPINION,

531
00:28:49,895 --> 00:28:51,397
AND I DIDN'T APPROVE
YOUR MODIFICATIONS.

532
00:28:51,438 --> 00:28:53,232
STOP WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

533
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:55,526
TRAVIS: PAUL.
PAUL: YOU HEARD ME.

534
00:28:57,236 --> 00:28:59,071
TRAVIS: I DIDN'T MEAN
TO UNDERMINE YOUR AUTHORITY.

535
00:28:59,112 --> 00:29:00,698
PAUL: REALLY?

536
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,616
TRAVIS: BUT YOU'RE
BEING UNREASONABLE.

537
00:29:02,658 --> 00:29:04,201
I JUST WANT US TO BE PREPARED.

538
00:29:04,243 --> 00:29:05,744
PAUL: US?

539
00:29:05,785 --> 00:29:07,787
YOU KEEP TALKING AS IF
YOU'RE A PART OF THIS CREW.

540
00:29:07,829 --> 00:29:09,582
TRAVIS: IT'S STILL MY HOME.

541
00:29:09,623 --> 00:29:11,584
PAUL: YOU TURNED YOUR BACK ON US
A LONG TIME AGO.

542
00:29:11,625 --> 00:29:16,213
TRAVIS: IS THAT WHAT THIS IS
ABOUT--ME LEAVING?

543
00:29:16,255 --> 00:29:18,757
IF YOU WANT TO BE
AN EFFECTIVE CAPTAIN,

544
00:29:18,798 --> 00:29:21,677
YOU'VE GOT TO SET
YOUR PERSONAL FEELINGS ASIDE,

545
00:29:21,719 --> 00:29:24,137
LISTEN TO WHAT OTHER PEOPLE
HAVE TO SAY.

546
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:27,849
PAUL: MORE WORDS OF WISDOM
FROM STARFLEET?

547
00:29:27,891 --> 00:29:30,977
TRAVIS: NO, YOUR FATHER.

548
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:34,106
HE SAID THAT TO ME
A LONG TIME AGO.

549
00:29:34,147 --> 00:29:36,900
IF HE WAS HERE NOW,
HE'D TELL YOU THE SAME THING.

550
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:39,528
PAUL: YOU QUOTING DAD?

551
00:29:39,570 --> 00:29:41,530
YOU NEVER LISTENED TO HIM.

552
00:29:41,572 --> 00:29:43,616
IF YOU HAD, YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE ABANDONED YOUR FAMILY.

553
00:29:43,657 --> 00:29:48,287
YOU BARELY SPOKE TO HIM
FOR THE LAST FOUR YEARS.

554
00:29:48,328 --> 00:29:50,289
YOU WEREN'T EVEN HERE
WHEN HE DIED.

555
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:54,876
TRAVIS: THAT ISN'T FAIR.

556
00:29:54,918 --> 00:29:58,046
PAUL: YOU KNEW HE WAS SICK.

557
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:02,301
BUT YOU DIDN'T REALLY CARE.

558
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:04,637
YOU ONLY DECIDED TO STOP BY

559
00:30:04,678 --> 00:30:07,264
BECAUSE IT WAS CONVENIENT
FOR YOU.

560
00:30:07,306 --> 00:30:09,516
HOSTILE ALIENS
AREN'T OUR PROBLEM.

561
00:30:09,558 --> 00:30:12,060
IT'S STARFLEET
AND PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

562
00:30:12,102 --> 00:30:15,397
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA HOW
HARD IT IS TO FIND NEW CREWMEN?

563
00:30:16,940 --> 00:30:20,319
NO ONE WANTS TO RUN
FREIGHT ANYMORE.

564
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,738
THEY ALL WANT TO BE EXPLORERS,

565
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:25,240
CRUISING AROUND
ON STATE-OF-THE-ART SHIPS

566
00:30:25,282 --> 00:30:27,200
WITH THEIR PERSONAL CHEFS.

567
00:30:27,242 --> 00:30:29,286
TRAVIS: YOU WANT TO STAND AROUND

568
00:30:29,328 --> 00:30:32,247
FEELING SORRY FOR YOURSELF,
GO AHEAD.

569
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:34,708
I'VE GOT BETTER THINGS TO DO.

570
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:40,255
PAUL: TAKE THOSE
UPGRADES OFFLINE.

571
00:30:40,297 --> 00:30:42,716
I'LL CONFINE YOU
TO QUARTERS IF I HAVE TO.

572
00:30:42,758 --> 00:30:45,302
TRAVIS: I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP YOU, PAUL.

573
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:47,179
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,

574
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,681
YOU COULD USE A LITTLE HELP
RIGHT NOW.

575
00:30:48,722 --> 00:30:50,474
PAUL: I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP.

576
00:30:50,516 --> 00:30:53,352
TRAVIS:
YOU WANT TO TAKE THEM OFFLINE?

577
00:30:53,393 --> 00:30:55,521
DO IT YOURSELF.

578
00:31:15,957 --> 00:31:18,836
RIANNA: I UNDERSTAND YOU MADE
A FEW MODIFICATIONS

579
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:21,463
TO THE IMPULSE RELAYS.

580
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:25,342
NEXT TIME, YOU MIGHT
WANT TO CHECK WITH ME.

581
00:31:25,384 --> 00:31:27,594
I AM THE CHIEF ENGINEER.

582
00:31:27,636 --> 00:31:29,304
TRAVIS: I KNEW
HOW PAUL WOULD REACT,

583
00:31:29,346 --> 00:31:31,181
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO DRAG YOU INTO IT.

584
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:32,932
[RIANNA CHUCKLES]

585
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:34,768
RIANNA: I'VE PLAYED REFEREE
BETWEEN YOU AND YOUR BROTHER

586
00:31:34,810 --> 00:31:36,687
FOR A LONG TIME.

587
00:31:36,729 --> 00:31:40,148
TRAVIS: NEVER THOUGHT I'D
ACTUALLY MISS THESE.

588
00:31:40,190 --> 00:31:42,067
RIANNA: NUTRI-PAKS?

589
00:31:42,108 --> 00:31:44,069
TRAVIS: NOT
JUST ANY NUTRI-PAK--

590
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,739
STRAWBERRY SHORTCAKE.

591
00:31:46,780 --> 00:31:49,324
THE FIRST TIME
I TASTED REAL SHORTCAKE

592
00:31:49,366 --> 00:31:51,410
WAS IN SAN FRANCISCO.

593
00:31:51,451 --> 00:31:53,579
IT JUST WASN'T THE SAME.

594
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:55,455
[RIANNA CHUCKLES]

595
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:58,041
RIANNA: I THINK THEY'VE RUINED
YOUR TASTE BUDS.

596
00:31:58,083 --> 00:32:01,253
TRAVIS: I WOULDN'T MIND
EATING LIKE THIS AGAIN.

597
00:32:03,756 --> 00:32:07,426
I'M THINKING ABOUT ASKING
FOR AN EXTENDED LEAVE.

598
00:32:07,467 --> 00:32:10,512
I'M SURE CAPTAIN ARCHER
WOULD APPROVE, CONSIDERING.

599
00:32:12,431 --> 00:32:14,140
RIANNA:
HOW LONG WOULD YOU STAY?

600
00:32:14,182 --> 00:32:15,768
TRAVIS:
AS LONG AS I'M NEEDED.

601
00:32:15,809 --> 00:32:18,562
RIANNA:
BUT YOU'RE NEEDED ON YOUR SHIP.

602
00:32:18,604 --> 00:32:20,980
TRAVIS:
I'M NOT THE ONLY HELM OFFICER.

603
00:32:21,022 --> 00:32:23,358
RIANNA: EVEN IF YOUR CAPTAIN
AGREES, IT COULD BE A LONG TIME

604
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,360
BEFORE "ENTERPRISE" IS
BACK THIS WAY AGAIN.

605
00:32:25,402 --> 00:32:27,613
TRAVIS:
THERE'S A LOT FOR ME TO DO HERE.

606
00:32:27,654 --> 00:32:30,323
I CAN HELP UPGRADE
THE GUIDANCE AND WARP SYSTEMS.

607
00:32:30,365 --> 00:32:31,991
WITH A LITTLE LUCK,
WE COULD MAKE "HORIZON"

608
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:34,703
THE FASTEST J-CLASS
IN THE FLEET.

609
00:32:34,745 --> 00:32:36,996
RIANNA: YOU'RE GONNA GIVE UP
YOUR CAREER, MOVE BACK HOME,

610
00:32:37,038 --> 00:32:39,040
AND TAKE ORDERS
FROM YOUR BROTHER?

611
00:32:39,082 --> 00:32:41,919
TRAVIS: MY CAREER'S THE LAST
THING ON MY MIND RIGHT NOW.

612
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:43,545
RIANNA:
HA HA! OH, CONGRATULATIONS.

613
00:32:43,587 --> 00:32:45,756
NOW YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S
LIKE TO BE A PARENT.

614
00:32:45,798 --> 00:32:47,800
[RIANNA CHUCKLES]

615
00:32:47,841 --> 00:32:51,428
I COULD SPEND EVERY WAKING
MINUTE WORRYING ABOUT YOU TWO.

616
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:55,223
BUT I'D NEVER GET
ANY WORK DONE.

617
00:32:55,265 --> 00:32:57,601
TRAVIS: HE'S NOT READY, MOM.

618
00:32:59,853 --> 00:33:02,940
RIANNA: YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN YOUR
FATHER WHEN HE TOOK OVER.

619
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,525
HE WAS A YEAR YOUNGER
THAN PAUL IS NOW.

620
00:33:05,567 --> 00:33:07,611
HE WAS AN ENGINEER.

621
00:33:07,653 --> 00:33:10,697
HE DIDN'T KNOW THE FIRST THING
ABOUT RUNNING A BRIDGE.

622
00:33:10,739 --> 00:33:12,574
WE FELL SO FAR BEHIND SCHEDULE,

623
00:33:12,616 --> 00:33:15,744
HE ALMOST LOST
HIS E.C.A. LICENSE.

624
00:33:15,786 --> 00:33:17,955
HE WANTED TO QUIT.
I WOULDN'T LET HIM.

625
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:22,709
YOUR BROTHER
JUST NEEDS SOME TIME.

626
00:33:22,751 --> 00:33:25,712
TRAVIS: YOU DON'T THINK
I SHOULD STAY?

627
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:28,590
RIANNA: DIDN'T WE HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION?

628
00:33:28,632 --> 00:33:31,760
IT WAS RIGHT HERE IN THIS ROOM,
FOUR YEARS AGO,

629
00:33:31,802 --> 00:33:34,012
WHEN YOU FIRST THOUGHT
ABOUT JOINING STARFLEET.

630
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:36,139
TRAVIS: A LOT HAS CHANGED
IN FOUR YEARS, MOM.

631
00:33:36,181 --> 00:33:39,601
RIANNA: THAT'S TRUE, AND A LOT
MORE'S GOING TO CHANGE.

632
00:33:39,643 --> 00:33:42,938
WILL WE BE TALKING ABOUT THIS
AGAIN IN ANOTHER FOUR YEARS?

633
00:33:44,982 --> 00:33:49,695
YOU'RE THE HELMSMAN OF
THE FIRST WARP 5 STARSHIP.

634
00:33:49,736 --> 00:33:52,531
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

635
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:54,491
EVERYONE HERE IS--

636
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:57,828
EVEN PAUL,
THOUGH HE WON'T ADMIT IT.

637
00:33:59,705 --> 00:34:02,123
IF YOU'LL INDULGE
A LITTLE MOTHERLY ADVICE,

638
00:34:02,165 --> 00:34:06,294
DON'T LET YOUR GUILT OVER
LEAVING GUIDE YOUR DECISION.

639
00:34:06,336 --> 00:34:09,840
TRAVIS:
I'LL TRY TO KEEP THAT IN MIND.

640
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:12,926
GOOD NIGHT.

641
00:34:12,968 --> 00:34:14,970
RIANNA: GOOD NIGHT.

642
00:34:24,103 --> 00:34:25,230
[TUCKER CHUCKLES]

643
00:34:25,271 --> 00:34:27,106
TUCKER: I FIND IT HARD
TO BELIEVE

644
00:34:27,148 --> 00:34:28,692
THAT NO ONE ON VULCAN'S EVER
HEARD OF A HORROR MOVIE.

645
00:34:28,734 --> 00:34:30,652
T'POL:
THERE IS SOMETHING SIMILAR--

646
00:34:30,694 --> 00:34:33,655
A DISCIPLINE
KNOWN AS TARUL-ETEK.

647
00:34:33,697 --> 00:34:38,577
IT USES DISTURBING IMAGERY TO
PROVOKE AN EMOTIONAL RESPONSE.

648
00:34:38,618 --> 00:34:40,829
ARCHER: THEY TRY AND SCARE YOU

649
00:34:40,871 --> 00:34:43,164
TO SEE HOW WELL YOU
SUPPRESS YOUR EMOTIONS.

650
00:34:43,206 --> 00:34:46,001
T'POL: I DON'T
UNDERSTAND WHY HUMANS

651
00:34:46,043 --> 00:34:48,378
WOULD FEEL COMPELLED
TO FRIGHTEN THEMSELVES.

652
00:34:50,255 --> 00:34:52,340
ARCHER:
GETS THE HEART PUMPING.

653
00:34:52,382 --> 00:34:56,344
T'POL: CARDIOVASCULAR ACTIVITY
WOULD BE MORE EFFICIENT.

654
00:34:56,386 --> 00:34:59,765
ARCHER: YOU NEVER DID GIVE
US YOUR OPINION OF THE MOVIE.

655
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:04,352
T'POL: THERE WERE
MANY MEDICAL INACCURACIES.

656
00:35:04,394 --> 00:35:07,773
TUCKER: WHAT DID YOU THINK
OF THE STORY?

657
00:35:11,985 --> 00:35:14,195
T'POL: I THOUGHT THE PROTAGONIST
WAS INTERESTING.

658
00:35:14,237 --> 00:35:18,241
TUCKER: DR. FRANKENSTEIN?
T'POL: NO, HIS CREATION.

659
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:20,827
FROM MY PERSPECTIVE,

660
00:35:20,869 --> 00:35:22,704
THIS WAS THE STORY
OF AN INDIVIDUAL

661
00:35:22,746 --> 00:35:24,998
PERSECUTED BY HUMANS
BECAUSE HE WAS DIFFERENT.

662
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,584
TUCKER: THAT'S ONE WAY
OF LOOKING AT IT.

663
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:31,546
T'POL: IN MANY WAYS,
THE FILM SEEMED QUITE PROPHETIC.

664
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:34,382
THE REACTION OF THE VILLAGERS,
FOR EXAMPLE--

665
00:35:34,424 --> 00:35:36,426
IT WAS SIMILAR TO THE RECEPTION
VULCANS RECEIVED

666
00:35:36,468 --> 00:35:38,344
AFTER LANDING ON EARTH.

667
00:35:38,386 --> 00:35:40,221
[ARCHER CHUCKLES]

668
00:35:40,263 --> 00:35:42,641
ARCHER: UH,
I DON'T RECALL ANYONE

669
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,434
GREETING THE VULCAN AMBASSADOR

670
00:35:44,476 --> 00:35:46,519
WITH TORCHES AND PITCHFORKS.

671
00:35:46,561 --> 00:35:49,856
T'POL: NEVERTHELESS, MANY HUMANS
REACTED WITH FEAR AND ANGER.

672
00:35:49,898 --> 00:35:52,025
ARCHER:
THEY DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO EXPECT.

673
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:55,821
T'POL: I'M GOING TO RECOMMEND

674
00:35:55,862 --> 00:35:57,530
THAT AMBASSADOR SOVAL
WATCH THE FILM.

675
00:35:57,572 --> 00:35:59,574
TUCKER: YOU'RE KIDDING.

676
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:01,576
T'POL:
I BELIEVE IT WOULD HELP VULCANS

677
00:36:01,618 --> 00:36:05,622
WHO'VE RECENTLY ARRIVED
ON EARTH.

678
00:36:05,664 --> 00:36:08,041
ARCHER: MAYBE INVITING
HER TO MOVIE NIGHT

679
00:36:08,083 --> 00:36:10,043
WASN'T SUCH A GREAT IDEA.

680
00:36:10,085 --> 00:36:11,795
T'POL: ON THE CONTRARY.

681
00:36:11,837 --> 00:36:15,256
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO
"BRIDE OF FRANKENSTEIN."

682
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:17,676
HOSHI: Bridge to Captain Archer.

683
00:36:17,717 --> 00:36:19,511
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.

684
00:36:19,552 --> 00:36:21,972
HOSHI: You might want to look
out the window, sir.

685
00:36:33,108 --> 00:36:34,693
[RUMBLING, COMPUTER BEEPS]

686
00:36:34,734 --> 00:36:36,653
REED: THERMAL SHEAR.

687
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:38,488
SOME OF THOSE ERUPTIONS ARE
GETTING CLOSE TO "ENTERPRISE."

688
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,281
ARCHER: TAKE US UP
ANOTHER 5,000 KILOMETERS.

689
00:36:40,323 --> 00:36:42,241
HELMSMAN: AYE, SIR.
T'POL: CAPTAIN.

690
00:36:42,283 --> 00:36:44,577
I'M READING BIO-SIGNS
ON THE PLANET.

691
00:36:44,619 --> 00:36:47,664
TO QUOTE DR. FRANKENSTEIN,
IT'S ALIVE.

692
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:49,833
ARCHER:
I THOUGHT IT WAS UNINHABITED.

693
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:51,543
T'POL: IT APPEARS
THAT SEVERAL MICROBIAL SPECIES

694
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:53,045
WHICH LIVE UNDERGROUND

695
00:36:53,086 --> 00:36:54,963
ARE BEING UNEARTHED
BY THE VOLCANIC ACTIVITY.

696
00:36:55,005 --> 00:36:57,174
ARCHER: SEE WHAT YOU CAN LEARN
ABOUT THEM.

697
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:04,305
PAUL:
FULL POWER TO THE HULL PLATING.

698
00:37:04,347 --> 00:37:05,682
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

699
00:37:05,724 --> 00:37:09,061
NICHOLS: WE'RE BEING HAILED.

700
00:37:09,102 --> 00:37:12,064
PAUL: THIS IS CAPTAIN MAYWEATHER
OF THE E.C.S. "HORIZON."

701
00:37:12,105 --> 00:37:13,940
ALIEN:<i> PREPARE TO SURRENDER</i>
<i>YOUR VESSEL</i>

702
00:37:13,982 --> 00:37:15,942
<i>AND EVACUATE THE CREW.</i>

703
00:37:15,984 --> 00:37:19,029
PAUL: I'LL GIVE YOU OUR CARGO,
BUT NOT OUR SHIP.

704
00:37:19,071 --> 00:37:21,280
ALIEN:<i> YOU WON'T BE HARMED</i>
<i>IF YOU COOPERATE.</i>

705
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:22,908
<i>DROP OUT OF WARP.</i>

706
00:37:22,949 --> 00:37:24,659
PAUL: WE'RE DOZENS OF
LIGHT-YEARS FROM OUR HOMEWORLD.

707
00:37:24,701 --> 00:37:27,079
THERE HAS TO BE
SOME COMPROMISE WE CAN--

708
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,872
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

709
00:37:28,914 --> 00:37:30,874
TRAVIS:
THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

710
00:37:34,586 --> 00:37:36,462
PAUL: BRING THE WEAPON UPGRADES
ONLINE.

711
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:38,757
STILL THINK YOU CAN
DISABLE THEIR ENGINES?

712
00:37:38,798 --> 00:37:40,341
TRAVIS: IF I CAN GET
A CLEAR SHOT.

713
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:42,677
BUT I CAN'T DO THAT
AS LONG AS THEY'RE BEHIND US.

714
00:37:42,719 --> 00:37:43,845
[ALARM]

715
00:37:43,887 --> 00:37:45,430
NICHOLS: THEY'VE HIT MODULE 5.

716
00:37:45,471 --> 00:37:47,557
TRAVIS: IT'S GOING TO BE TOUGH
TO MANEUVER

717
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:48,975
WITH 30 KILOTONS OF CARGO.

718
00:37:49,017 --> 00:37:50,810
WE'VE GOT TO CUT IT LOOSE.

719
00:37:57,483 --> 00:38:01,238
RIANNA: ENGINEERING, STAND BY
TO RELEASE THE PRIMARY CLAMPS.

720
00:38:01,279 --> 00:38:03,031
PAUL: YOU DO REMEMBER
HOW TO FLY THIS SHIP.

721
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:06,701
TRAVIS:
I'M SURE IT'LL COME BACK TO ME.

722
00:38:10,496 --> 00:38:12,457
PAUL: TAKE US OUT OF WARP.

723
00:38:18,004 --> 00:38:19,756
RELEASE THE CLAMPS.

724
00:38:22,008 --> 00:38:24,177
TRAVIS: THEY'RE CLOSING.

725
00:38:24,219 --> 00:38:26,846
40 METERS. 30.

726
00:38:26,888 --> 00:38:28,598
RIANNA: JUST A FEW MORE CLAMPS.

727
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,642
TRAVIS: 10 METERS.

728
00:38:42,112 --> 00:38:44,281
[ALARM]

729
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:45,782
RIANNA:
STARBOARD PLATING'S DOWN.

730
00:38:45,824 --> 00:38:47,659
PAUL: TRAVIS!

731
00:38:58,837 --> 00:39:00,880
RIANNA: HULL PLATING'S GONE.

732
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:03,008
TRAVIS: I'M COMING AROUND AGAIN.

733
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:12,058
NICHOLS:
THEIR WEAPONS ARE GOING DOWN.

734
00:39:12,100 --> 00:39:16,229
PAUL: KEEP OUR TURRETS
LOCKED ON THEM. OPEN A CHANNEL.

735
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:18,439
THIS IS CAPTAIN MAYWEATHER.

736
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:21,526
I'D THINK TWICE BEFORE ATTACKING
ANY OF OUR SHIPS AGAIN.

737
00:39:22,902 --> 00:39:24,946
REDOCK WITH THE CARGO SECTION.

738
00:39:24,988 --> 00:39:27,532
THEN GET US OUT OF HERE.

739
00:39:27,573 --> 00:39:29,784
TRAVIS: AYE, CAPTAIN.

740
00:39:41,671 --> 00:39:43,631
[DOOR BUZZES]

741
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:44,924
COME IN.

742
00:39:49,304 --> 00:39:51,264
PAUL: ALL PACKED?

743
00:39:51,306 --> 00:39:53,558
TRAVIS: WOULDN'T WANT
TO WEAR OUT MY WELCOME.

744
00:39:54,976 --> 00:39:56,602
PAUL: I GOT A MESSAGE
FROM "ENTERPRISE."

745
00:39:56,644 --> 00:39:58,313
THEY'RE RUNNING AHEAD
OF SCHEDULE.

746
00:39:58,355 --> 00:40:01,440
WE'LL BE DOCKING
IN ABOUT 20 MINUTES.

747
00:40:01,482 --> 00:40:04,277
TRAVIS: IF YOU LIKE, I'LL SPEAK
WITH LIEUTENANT REED.

748
00:40:04,319 --> 00:40:06,779
I'M SURE HE CAN HELP YOU
REMOVE THAT ALIEN BEACON.

749
00:40:06,821 --> 00:40:08,948
PAUL: THANKS.

750
00:40:13,452 --> 00:40:16,664
SO DID YOU EVER MAKE IT
TO TRELKIS III?

751
00:40:16,706 --> 00:40:18,457
TRAVIS: WHAT?

752
00:40:18,499 --> 00:40:22,254
PAUL: TRELKIS III--THE PLANET
WITH THE MULTICENTRIC RINGS.

753
00:40:22,295 --> 00:40:25,590
YOU USED TO TALK ABOUT IT
WHEN WE WERE GROWING UP.

754
00:40:25,631 --> 00:40:27,842
TRAVIS: WE HAVEN'T TRAVELED
QUITE THAT FAR.

755
00:40:27,884 --> 00:40:29,886
PAUL: WELL, WHEN YOU DO...

756
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:32,889
HOW ABOUT SENDING ME
A SUBSPACE POSTCARD?

757
00:40:32,931 --> 00:40:35,725
TRAVIS: YOU CAN COUNT ON IT.

758
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:46,278
PAUL: WELL, I'D BETTER GET BACK
TO THE BRIDGE.

759
00:40:51,074 --> 00:40:53,534
SEE YOU IN ANOTHER FOUR YEARS?

760
00:40:53,576 --> 00:40:55,828
TRAVIS: MAYBE SOONER.

761
00:40:57,330 --> 00:40:59,416
PAUL: I'D LIKE THAT.

762
00:41:21,646 --> 00:41:24,232
ARCHER: WELCOME BACK.
TRAVIS: THANK YOU, SIR.

763
00:41:24,274 --> 00:41:27,610
ARCHER: HOW'S YOUR FAMILY?
TRAVIS: THEY'RE OK.

764
00:41:27,652 --> 00:41:32,449
ARCHER: WE SPOTTED SOME DAMAGE
ON THEIR PORT CARGO MODULES.

765
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:36,577
TRAVIS: PROBABLY AN OLD
METEORITE IMPACT.

766
00:41:38,121 --> 00:41:40,498
ARCHER: YOU SURE
EVERYTHING'S ALL RIGHT?

767
00:41:43,042 --> 00:41:45,295
TRAVIS: NEVER BETTER, SIR.
